snippet.textDisplay: So Rashid, it's not a Flipper, so don't call it a Flipper. Give it another name. Flippers have been around since the days of lob bowling and they've been executed in the same way with the finger click and recorded as such in books for over a century, don't try passing off some Mickey Mouse delivery as something that it's not - it's like the 'Slider' nonsense, there's no such thing as a slider it's either an 'Orthodox back-spinner' or a Leg Break gone wrong. If you've got some Mickey mouse straight ball,  just refer to it as the one that goes on straight.

snippet.textDisplay:
Those thinking that the Australians will now be able to decode Rashid, he has been playing in the IPL for years now.

Indian batsmen are generally good players of spin and they have played with and against him multiple times now. If that was the case, he should have fallen flat by now but he has not. Still he goes all in in T20s in the ipl.

So, it is not just about knowing his varieties. Those are already known by facing him and by aid of latest technologies. It is about developing the skills to counter him when it comes to match situation.
snippet.textOriginal:
